      <description>Philip Mason joined the Indian Civil Service in 1928 and served as
            Assistant Magistrate in the United Provinces, Under-Secretary in the War Department,
            Deputy Commissioner in the Himalayan district of Garhwal, Deputy Secretary in the
            Defense and War Department, Secretary to the Chiefs of Staff Committee, and Joint
            Secretary to the War Department. He ended his career when India gained independence. He
            was a well-known writer of many books, many focusing on India.</description>
